<%- include('partials/head', {
  title,
  metaTitle,
  metaDescription,
  canonicalPath
}) %>

<%- include('partials/header') %>

<%
  const s = settings || {};
  const phoneRaw = String(s.phone || "").trim();
  const phoneTel = phoneRaw.replace(/\s+/g, "");
%>

<div class="wrap">
  <div class="card">
    <h1>Truck Hearse Case Studies</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      This page is designed to showcase real completed services involving our truck hearses and lorry hearses,
      and will continue to grow as additional case studies are published.
    </p>

    <div class="cta" style="margin:18px 0 8px;">
      <a class="btn" href="/contact">Enquire</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/gallery">View gallery</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/faq">FAQ</a>
      <% if (phoneTel) { %>
        <a class="btn" href="tel:<%= phoneTel %>">Call <%= phoneRaw %></a>
      <% } %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title">Why case studies matter</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        Case studies help families and funeral directors understand how alternative funeral transport can be used
        in a respectful, professional, and meaningful way. They show the type of funeral each vehicle may suit,
        the kind of tribute it helps create, and why a specialist hearse may feel more fitting than a traditional option.
      </p>
      <p>
        For many people, reading about real completed services provides reassurance that a truck hearse or lorry hearse
        can become an important and dignified part of the final journey.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title">What future case studies will include</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        As this page develops, each case study can include the vehicle used, the general area served, the type of tribute
        requested, and the reason the chosen hearse was especially suitable. This helps demonstrate how different vehicles
        support different kinds of funerals across the UK.
      </p>
      <p>
        It also creates useful, relevant content for families searching for truck hearse hire, lorry hearse hire,
        and alternative funeral transport that feels more personal and distinctive.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title">Current specialist vehicles</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p><a href="/renault-magnum-hearse">Renault Magnum hearse</a></p>
      <p><a href="/erf-ec12-hearse">ERF EC12 hearse</a></p>
      <p><a href="/lorry-hearse-hire-uk">Lorry hearse hire across the UK</a></p>
      <p><a href="/truck-hearse-vs-traditional-hearse">Truck hearse vs traditional hearse</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title">Preparing real completed service write-ups</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        When you are ready, this page can be expanded with individual case study entries based on real completed services.
        That is the best long-term approach for both trust and SEO, because it adds original content based on genuine work
        rather than generic wording alone.
      </p>
      <p>
        A good case study can describe the type of funeral, the chosen hearse, the reason it suited the service,
        and the area covered, while keeping the write-up respectful and appropriate.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <% /* 
    Future real case study template — duplicate this block and replace with genuine details only.

    <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
      <h2 class="section-title">Case study: [Vehicle] for a funeral in [Area]</h2>
      <div class="rich">
        <p>
          [Write a factual summary of the completed service. Avoid private or sensitive details unless you have permission.]
        </p>
        <p>
          [Explain why the chosen vehicle was fitting and how it supported a personal final journey.]
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  */ %>
</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
